Base:Descriptions.Base:Description:
{? | $(this.trait:color) | $(this.trait:color)}{? | $(this.trait:material) | $(this.trait:material)} $(this.trait:brief). This piece of furniture is a long, flat-topped fixture in a shop or bank across which business is conducted with customers. Alternatively, this type of furniture is sometimes even used in kitchens as a surface on which to prepare foods. This counter boasts a smooth top, $(this.trait:color) $(this.trait:material) sides, front panel, and three cupboards beneath for storage.{? | $(this.trait:surface:material) | The entire top of the $(this.trait:color) $(this.trait:material) $(this.trait:brief) has been covered end to end in $(this.trait:surface:type) $(this.trait:surface:color) $(this.trait:surface:material), lending the furniture a varied taste of opulence.}
{? | $(this.trait:figurine:material) | A carved, $(this.trait:figurine:color) $(this.trait:figurine:material) $(this.trait:figurine:type) relief has been centrally set against a wide $(this.trait:material) backdrop that composes the front of the $(this.trait:brief). Matching the $(this.trait:figurine:type), the edging surrounding the counter has been carved into a decorative relief of $(this.trait:figurine:material) acanthus leaves.}{? | $(this.trait:statue:material) | Either end of the $(this.trait:material) $(this.trait:brief) is supported from below by $(this.trait:statue:material) columns, delicately tooled into the shape of $(this.trait:statue:type)s. The $(this.trait:statue:type)s are encased; top, bottom, and sides by a framework of $(this.trait:figurine:material) acanthus relief edging.}{? | $(this.trait:engraving) | $(this.trait:engraving).}
$(this.quality_description)
